# <%@meta name="title"%>

This document explains how to (bi-directionally) access your [R-Forge] repository using [Git] instead of [Subversion].

Quick summary:
1. `svn checkout` => `git svn clone <url>`
2. `svn update`   => `git svn rebase`
3. `svn commit`   => `git svn dcommit`



> git svn clone svn+ssh://henrikb@svn.r-forge.r-project.org/svnroot/r-dots/pkg/R.synchronize .

Initialized empty Git repository in x:/_GITHUB/R-Forge exports/r-dots/foo/R.methodsS3/R.menu/.git/
